test: \u003E50% suppression of cortisol\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Adrenal cortical adenoma","Ectopic ACTH-secreting tumour","Pituitary ACTH-secreting adenoma","Bilateral adrenal hyperplasia","Factitious Cushing\u0027s syndrome"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe pattern of results indicates \u003Cstrong\u003Epituitary ACTH-secreting adenoma\u003C/strong\u003E (Cushing\u0027s disease). Key findings supporting this diagnosis are:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EElevated ACTH levels\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EFailure to suppress with low-dose dexamethasone\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003ESuppression with high-dose dexamethasone\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAdrenal cortical adenoma\u003C/strong\u003E would show suppressed ACTH levels due to negative feedback\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEctopic ACTH-secreting tumour\u003C/strong\u003E typically shows very high ACTH levels and fails to suppress with high-dose dexamethasone\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBilateral adrenal hyperplasia\u003C/strong\u003E is usually ACTH-independent with low ACTH levels\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFactitious Cushing\u0027s syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E would show suppressed ACTH and cortisol due to exogenous glucocorticoid use\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003E50% suppression with high-dose dexamethasone is characteristic of pituitary sources, as these retain some sensitivity to glucocorticoid negative feedback.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Cushing\u0027s disease (pituitary ACTH-secreting adenoma) shows high ACTH levels and suppression with high-dose dexamethasone testing.","The dexamethasone suppression test pattern helps differentiate between pituitary, ectopic, and adrenal causes of Cushing\u0027s syndrome.","Primary adrenal causes of Cushing\u0027s syndrome show suppressed ACTH levels due to negative feedback."],"references":["Raff H, Carroll T. Cushing\u0027s syndrome: from physiological principles to diagnosis and clinical care. J Physiol. 2015 Feb 1;593(3):493-506. doi: 10.1113/jphysiol.2014.282871. Epub 2015 Jan 5. PMID: 25480800; PMCID: PMC4324701.","Nieman LK. Recent Updates on the Diagnosis and Management of Cushing\u0027s Syndrome. Endocrinol Metab (Seoul). 2018 Jun;33(2):139-146. doi: 10.3803/EnM.2018.33.2.139. PMID: 29947171; PMCID: PMC6021313.","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Wass, J. A., \u0026 Stewart, P. M. (Eds.). (2011). Oxford textbook of endocrinology and diabetes. Oxford University Press, USA"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56495"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15644"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56495","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56495"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-16T18:59:50+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-16T19:00:57+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8335"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71024"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10: